Sentencas: (Ba0.5Sr0.5)(1-x)CaxCo0.8Fe0.2O3-delta (BSCCF), (Ba0.5Sr0.5)(0.8)La0.2Co0.8Fe0.2O3-delta (BSLCF), and (Ba0.5Sr0.5)(0.8)La0.2-xCaxCo0.8Fe0.2O3-delta (BSLCCF) perovskite oxides were synthesized by the modified citrate method and characterized by X-ray diffraction (XRD) and scanning electron microscopy (SEM).
Titulo: Influence of Cation Dopants in the A-Site on the Crystal Structure, Microstructure, and Electrical Conductivity of Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ as a New Solid-Oxide-Fuel-Cell Cathode

Sentencas: These oxides showed primarily a cubic phase with their dense bodies after sintering.
Titulo: Influence of Cation Dopants in the A-Site on the Crystal Structure, Microstructure, and Electrical Conductivity of Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ as a New Solid-Oxide-Fuel-Cell Cathode

Sentencas: The lattice parameter was decreased with increasing Ca2+-ion content in BSCCF.
Titulo: Influence of Cation Dopants in the A-Site on the Crystal Structure, Microstructure, and Electrical Conductivity of Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ as a New Solid-Oxide-Fuel-Cell Cathode

Sentencas: Conversely, the substitution of Ca2+ ions for La3+ ions in BSLCCF increased the lattice parameter.
Titulo: Influence of Cation Dopants in the A-Site on the Crystal Structure, Microstructure, and Electrical Conductivity of Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ as a New Solid-Oxide-Fuel-Cell Cathode

Sentencas: The maximum electrical conductivities were 96 S.cm(-1) at 650 degrees C for the 30 mol% Ca2+-substituted BSCCF and 353 S.cm(-1) at 350 degrees C for BSLCF.
Titulo: Influence of Cation Dopants in the A-Site on the Crystal Structure, Microstructure, and Electrical Conductivity of Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ as a New Solid-Oxide-Fuel-Cell Cathode

Sentencas: The thermal expansion coefficient (TEC) of BSCCF was almost constant regardless of the Ca2+-ion contents, whereas that of BSLCCF decreased with decreasing Ca2+-ion content.
Titulo: Influence of Cation Dopants in the A-Site on the Crystal Structure, Microstructure, and Electrical Conductivity of Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ as a New Solid-Oxide-Fuel-Cell Cathode
